Paper: hep-th/0105153

Date: 2001-05-16

Title: (De)Constructing Dimensions and Non-commutative Geometry

Authors: Mohsen Alishahiha

Comments: 14 pages, latex; references added

Journal-ref: Phys.Lett. B517 (2001) 406-414

In this paper the model considered by Arkani-Hamed, Cohen and Georgi in thecontext of (de)constructing dimensions has been studied by making use ofnon-commutative geometry. The non-commutative geometry provides a naturalframework to study this model with or without gravity.